gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 111, Clippers 97
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeat the Clippers, 111-97. Julius Randle led the Knicks with 27 points and 10 rebounds as RJ Barrett (26 points, six rebounds, and four assists) and Mitchell Robinson (13 points, 15 rebounds) totaled 39 points. Kawhi Leonard led the Clippers with 18 points, five rebounds, and three assists while James Harden (17 points, 6 assists) and Russell Westbrook (17 points, four rebounds, four assists) combined for 34 points. The Knicks improve to 3-4 as the Clippers move to 3-3.
